itude of forms and sometimes in a form that is seemingly in=\r\nfinite. Again God can come to a seeker not as a form but as a Light. Etc. M=\r\nany possibilities. That is why it is called God. He/She/it is beyond\n ALL l=\r\nimits, yet it rejects no option, that humans may impose on it through their=\r\n minds or their experiences, spiritual or otherwise.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=\r\n=3D&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia; background-=\r\ncolor: transparent; font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-family: Georgi=\r\na; line-height: 19.515625px; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=\r\n=3D&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; font-family: Georgia; background-=\r\ncolor: transparent; font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-family: Georgi=\r\na; line-height: 19.515625px; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;This thing called God is bes=\r\nt described by one adjective - Infinite. And the basic character of Infinit=\r\ny is that it can&#39;t be totally understood by anyone. You can only understand=\r\n some parts of it, every the entirety. Being Infinite, it is beyond restric=\r\ntions. So it is both with form and without form. And at times even simultan=\r\neously. [Sounds illogical no? But Infinity was anyway, even in\n mathematics=\r\n, never within the purview of normal logic.]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;colo=\r\nr: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia; background-color: t=\r\nransparent; font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-family: Georgia; line-=\r\nheight: 19.515625px; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color=\r\n: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; font-family: Georgia; background-color: tr=\r\nansparent; font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-family: Georgia; line-h=\r\neight: 19.515625px; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;It is only the limitations of the see=\r\nker which limits the experience of God in all its totality. He/She/It is th=\r\ne sum total of all that is imaginable, all that is difficult to imagine and=\r\n all that just cannot be humanly imagined. Forms, therefore, get included i=\r\nnside it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12pt; f=\r\nont-family: Georgia; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;s=\r\npan style=3D&quot;font-family: Georgia; line-height: 19.515625px;\n font-size: 12=\r\npt;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; f=\r\nont-family: Georgia; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;s=\r\npan style=3D&quot;line-height: 19.515625px;&quot;&gt;Of forms again there are various ch=\r\naracteristics. Not all forms are similar. The same devata can appear in two=\r\n different nature of form depending on the seeker, one maybe more sutble th=\r\nan the other.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16p=\r\nx; font-family: Georgia; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal;=\r\n&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;line-height: 19.515625px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;=\r\ncolor: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; font-family: Georgia; background-colo=\r\nr: transparent; font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;line-height: 19.515625p=\r\nx;&quot;&gt;Basically noting every single possibility makes it tremendously complic=\r\nated, but bottomline is that God is both with form and also without form. A=\r\nnd one is not necessarily higher than the other aspect of\n God.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div=\r\n&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; font-family: Georgia; =\r\nbackground-color: transparent; font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;line-hei=\r\nght: 19.515625px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3